{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T11:01:58.143Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Vanishing Gradient Fix Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"vanishing gradient fix"},{"type":"text","text":" in LSTM and GRU refers to the architectural innovations that allow these networks to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"sidestep the vanishing gradient problem"},{"type":"text","text":" that plagued traditional RNNs, enabling them to learn long-term dependencies in sequential data. Traditional RNNs suffer because gradients become exponentially smaller as they backpropagate through time, causing the network to \"forget\" early sequence information."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Vanishing Gradient Matters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The vanishing gradient problem is central to why RNNs fail on long sequences:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Problem"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Impact"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Gradients fade"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Gradients used to update weights show a decreasing trend as they move back in time"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Error signal disappears"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Signal becomes exponentially smaller as it passes through many layers"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Cannot learn long-term dependencies"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Network struggles to recall dependencies over extended sequences"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example"},{"type":"text","text":": In a paragraph, the network understands the last sentence but \"forgets\" the first sentence entirely."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How LSTM Fixes Vanishing Gradients"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The key mechanisms:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Additive Cell State Update"},{"type":"text","text":" (Not Multiplicative)"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In traditional RNNs:\n\\[\nh_t = \\tanh(W \\cdot h"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"{t-1} + U \\cdot x_t)\n\\]\nInformation is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"italic"}],"text":"multiplied"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":" repeatedly through nonlinearities, causing gradients to vanish exponentially."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In LSTM:\n\\[\nC_t = C"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"{t-1} \\odot f_t + \\tilde{C}"},{"type":"text","text":"t \\odot i_t\n\\]\nThe cell state update is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"additive"},{"type":"text","text":", not multiplicative. This allows gradients to flow "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"without being significantly attenuated"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Direct Gradient Path via Cell State"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"LSTM has a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"cell state ("},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"C_t"}},{"type":"text","text":")"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" that acts like a conveyor belt:\n- Information flows straight through the sequence\n- Only experiences "},{"type":"text","text":"linear interactions"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" (element-wise multiplication by gates)\n- No repeated nonlinearities crushing the gradient"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conveyor Belt:\n═══════════════════════════════\n  C₀ → C₁ → C₂ → ... → Cₙ\n  │    │    │         │\n  ▼    ▼    ▼         ▼\nLinear × Gate      Linear × Gate\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nGradients pass through without vanishing."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The cell state is a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"stable memory unit"},{"type":"text","text":" that allows gradients to flow through the network without significant attenuation."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Gating Mechanism"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"LSTMs use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3 gates"},{"type":"text","text":" that regulate information flow:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Gate"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Function"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sigmoid Output"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Forget Gate"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Decides what to remove from cell state"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"0 (forget) to 1 (keep)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Input Gate"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Decides what new information to add"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"0 to 1"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Output Gate"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Decides what to output"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"0 to 1"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How it works"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- When forget gate ≈ 1: Keep old state (gradient flows unchanged)\n- When forget gate ≈ 0: Forget old state (gradient path blocked)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The gating mechanism allows the network to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"selectively remember data from previous time steps"},{"type":"text","text":", preventing the signal from disappearing."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How GRU Fixes Vanishing Gradients"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"GRU uses a similar but simplified approach:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Update Gate"},{"type":"text","text":" (Combines Forget + Input)"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"GRU's update gate equation:\n\\[\nh_t = (1 - z_t) \\odot h"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"{t-1} + z_t \\odot \\tilde{h}"},{"type":"text","text":"t\n\\]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key insight"},{"type":"text","text":": Information is passed from time step to time step "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"without having to pass through a nonlinearity"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"blockMath","attrs":{"latex":"- When \\( z_t \\approx 0 \\): \\( h_t \\approx h_{t-1} \\) (retain old state)"}},{"type":"blockMath","attrs":{"latex":"- When \\( z_t \\approx 1 \\): \\( h_t \\approx \\tilde{h}_t \\) (replace with new state)"}},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This sidesteps vanishing gradients the same way LSTM does—the update path avoids repeated nonlinearities."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Single Hidden State"},{"type":"text","text":" (No Separate Cell State)"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"GRU doesn't have a separate cell state like LSTM. Instead:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Hidden state ("},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"h_t"}},{"type":"text","text":")"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" combines both long-term and short-term memory\n- Still uses gating to control gradient flow\n- Simpler architecture but same gradient-stabilizing effect"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The main shared idea between LSTM and GRU is that "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"information can be passed on from time step to time step without passing through a nonlinearity"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Core Fix: Avoiding Repeated Nonlinearities"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The root cause of vanishing gradients:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In backpropagation through time, the gradient is:\n\\[\n\\text{gradient} = \\prod"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"{i=1}^{t} \\frac{\\partial \\text{activation}"},{"type":"text","text":"i}{\\partial \\text{activation}"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"{i-1}}\n\\]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"product of many small derivatives"},{"type":"text","text":". If each derivative is < 1 (e.g., 0.25 for sigmoid), the product shrinks exponentially as sequence length increases."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The LSTM/GRU solution:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both architectures allow information to flow with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"only linear (multiplicative by gates) interactions"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Gates use sigmoid (0–1), but they multiply the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"gate output"},{"type":"text","text":" with the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"state"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- The state itself passes through "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"additive updates"},{"type":"text","text":", not repeated nonlinearities\n- Gradients flow through the \"straight path\" of the state without being squared"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Traditional RNN:\n  h₀ → nonlinearity → h₁ → nonlinearity → h₂ → ... → hₙ\n  (Gradients crushed: derivative × derivative × derivative...)\n\nLSTM/GRU:\n  C₀ → linear × gate → C₁ → linear × gate → C₂ → ... → Cₙ\n  (Gradients flow: no repeated nonlinearities)"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"LSTM vs. GRU Gradient Fix Comparison"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Feature"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"LSTM"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"GRU"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Gating Mechanism"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"3 gates (forget, input, output)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"2 gates (update, reset)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Memory Path"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Separate cell state "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"C_t"}}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Single hidden state "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"h_t"}}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Update Type"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Additive: "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"C_t = C_{t-1} \\odot f_t + \\tilde{C}_t \\odot i_t"}}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Blend: "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"h_t = (1-z_t) \\odot h_{t-1} + z_t \\odot \\tilde{h}_t"}}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Gradient Fix"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Additive cell state + gating"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Update gate + gating"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Simplicity"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"More complex"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"More efficient"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both achieve the same goal: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"sidestepping the vanishing gradient problem"},{"type":"text","text":" through gating mechanisms."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefits of the Fix"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefit"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Explanation"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Learn long-term dependencies"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can capture relationships across very long sequences"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Stable gradient flow"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Gradients don't vanish exponentially through time"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Effective training"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Network can learn from entire sequence, not just recent parts"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Handle complex patterns"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Model complex sequential relationships in text, speech, time series"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"NLP success"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Essential for language modeling, translation, text generation"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental Model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of the vanishing gradient fix as "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"building a highway for information"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Traditional RNN"},{"type":"text","text":": Information travels through narrow, winding roads (nonlinearities) that get progressively narrower. Signals get lost along the journey."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"LSTM/GRU"},{"type":"text","text":": Information travels on a straight highway (cell state/hidden state) with toll gates (gating) that control what passes through. The highway stays the same width, so signals reach the destination."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Or think of it as "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"water pipes"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Traditional RNN"},{"type":"text","text":": Water (gradients) flows through many small valves (nonlinearities) that shrink the flow exponentially."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"LSTM/GRU"},{"type":"text","text":": Water flows through a large pipe (state) with open/close valves (gates) that control flow but don't shrink it."}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Vanishing gradients"},{"type":"text","text":" occur because gradients become exponentially smaller when backpropagating through many time steps (product of small derivatives)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"LSTM fixes it"},{"type":"text","text":" via "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"additive cell state updates"},{"type":"text","text":" (not multiplicative) + gating mechanisms that allow linear gradient flow"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"GRU fixes it"},{"type":"text","text":" via "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"update gate blending"},{"type":"text","text":" (old + new state) + gating that avoids repeated nonlinearities"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"core fix"},{"type":"text","text":": Information passes from time step to time step "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"without passing through a nonlinearity"},{"type":"text","text":", preventing gradient crushing"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Cell state"},{"type":"text","text":" (LSTM) or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"hidden state"},{"type":"text","text":" (GRU) acts as a stable path for gradients to flow through the entire sequence"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Gating mechanisms"},{"type":"text","text":" allow networks to selectively remember/forget data, preventing signal disappearance"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This enables "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"learning long-term dependencies"},{"type":"text","text":", essential for NLP, speech recognition, and time series analysis"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both LSTM and GRU "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"outperform standard RNNs significantly"},{"type":"text","text":" for processing sequential data because they solve the vanishing gradient problem"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The vanishing gradient fix is what makes LSTMs and GRUs capable of remembering context over long sequences, enabling models to understand entire conversations and documents—critical for generative AI tasks."}]}]}}
